# Backend (FastAPI)

- Mirror existing router → service → schema layering; logic in `services/`, not routers.
- Keep API contracts stable unless the task requires breaking changes.
- Validate inputs; return clear HTTP errors (401/403/404/422); no raw stack traces to clients.
- Preserve async where already used.

## Sensitive domains

Publication, visibility, route eligibility, import jobs, reconciliation, destination membership — read current code and tests before changing; prefer flags and compatibility layers over big-bang edits.

## DB

Model changes → Alembic migration + fixture updates. SQLite test DB: use `batch_alter_table` patterns from existing migrations when adding FKs.

## Tests

- New behavior → pytest in `tests/` (`*_new` suffix for new tests per project convention).
- No production-only assumptions in unit tests; use `conftest.py` factories.
- Run: `.venv/bin/python -m pytest <target> -q --no-cov`
